## Task 3 — Data Pipeline Documentation

### Written Explanation

1. **Dataset Collection** — Two HuggingFace datasets are downloaded: `twitter-financial-news-sentiment` (9,543 legitimate) and `sms_spam` (747 scam records, filtered for spam-only class). Merged into a 10,290-record CSV.

2. **Data Cleaning** — Text is lowercased, URLs removed, punctuation stripped, and extra whitespace collapsed. Empty records are dropped.

3. **Text Preprocessing** — Cleaned text stored in [cleaned_scam_dataset.csv](file:///c:/Users/TANMAY/OneDrive/Desktop/scam-detection-project/datasets/cleaned_scam_dataset.csv) with `cleaned_text` column alongside original [text](file:///c:/Users/TANMAY/OneDrive/Desktop/scam-detection-project/backend/main.py#44-50) and `label`.

4. **Feature Extraction** — Dual features extracted:
   - **TF-IDF:** 10,000-feature sparse matrix via `TfidfVectorizer` with English stop words removed.
   - **FinBERT:** 768-dimensional dense embeddings from `ProsusAI/finbert` using CLS token pooling, processed in batches of 128.

5. **Model Training** — 4 models trained on each feature set (where applicable) with stratified 80/20 split and class imbalance handling via `class_weight='balanced'` (LR) and `scale_pos_weight` (XGBoost).

6. **Model Evaluation** — Accuracy, recall, precision, F1 score, and confusion matrix computed. Logistic Regression on FinBERT selected as primary model (99.3% accuracy, 95.9% scam recall).

7. **Model Saving** — Models serialized via Joblib as [.pkl](file:///c:/Users/TANMAY/OneDrive/Desktop/scam-detection-project/datasets/X_tfidf.pkl) files into `model_files/` for API loading.

### Data Pipeline Flowchart

```mermaid
