## Task 4 — Machine Learning Pipeline Documentation

### Pipeline Steps

1. **Dataset Preparation** — Stratified 80/20 train-test split with `random_state=42` ensuring reproducibility. Class imbalance (92.7% legitimate vs 7.3% scam) handled via `class_weight='balanced'` for LR and `scale_pos_weight` for XGBoost.

2. **TF-IDF Vectorization** — `TfidfVectorizer(max_features=10000, stop_words='english')` transforms cleaned text into a sparse features matrix. Vectorizer saved for inference.

3. **FinBERT Embedding** — `ProsusAI/finbert` tokenizer + model extracts CLS-token embeddings (768 dimensions) with GPU acceleration, batch size 128.

4. **Model Training** — Four models trained on each feature set:
   - Logistic Regression (balanced class weights, max 1000 iterations)
   - Naive Bayes (MultinomialNB — TF-IDF only, cannot handle negative FinBERT values)
   - XGBoost (GPU CUDA, `scale_pos_weight` for class imbalance)
   - Voting Classifier (soft voting ensemble)

5. **Model Comparison & Selection** — All models compared on accuracy and scam recall.

### Model Comparison Table

| Model | Features | Accuracy | Scam Recall | Precision | F1 Score |
|-------|----------|----------|-------------|-----------|----------|
| Logistic Regression | TF-IDF | ~98.5% | ~89% | High | High |
| Naive Bayes | TF-IDF | 98.6% | 81.8% | High | High |
| XGBoost (GPU) | TF-IDF | 99.2% | 89.9% | High | High |
| Voting Classifier | TF-IDF | 98.1% | 75.1% | High | Moderate |
| XGBoost (GPU) | FinBERT | 99.1% | 90.6% | High | High |
| **Logistic Regression** ⭐ | **FinBERT** | **99.3%** | **95.9%** | **High** | **High** |

### Why Logistic Regression on FinBERT Was Selected

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Recall is the most critical metric for fraud detection.** A false negative (missed scam) can cause real financial harm. LR on FinBERT achieves **95.9% scam recall** — the highest across all models.

| Reason | Explanation |
|--------|-------------|
| **Highest Recall** | 95.9% vs. XGBoost FinBERT's 90.6% — catches 5.3% more scams |
| **Semantic Understanding** | FinBERT understands financial context, not just keywords |
| **Domain-Specific** | Pre-trained on financial text (ProsusAI/finbert) |
| **Simplicity** | LR is interpretable, fast, and lightweight for API serving |

### API Ensemble Strategy

In the production API, both engines run in parallel and their scam probabilities are averaged (50/50 weighted):

```
final_probability = 0.5 × P(scam | TF-IDF + XGBoost) + 0.5 × P(scam | FinBERT + LR)
```

This combines **keyword-level** detection (TF-IDF catches explicit scam words) with **semantic-level** detection (FinBERT understands context even without scam keywords).

