### 5.3 Prediction Workflow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["User enters text"] --> B["click Analyze Now"]
    B --> C["POST /predict with JSON body"]
    C --> D["Backend: clean_text()"]
    D --> E["Engine 1: TF-IDF transform → XGBoost predict_proba"]
    D --> F["Engine 2: FinBERT tokenize → CLS embed → LR predict_proba"]
    E --> G["prob_tfidf"]
    F --> H["prob_finbert"]
    G --> I["Ensemble: 0.5 × prob_tfidf + 0.5 × prob_finbert"]
    H --> I
    I --> J{"prob > 0.5?"}
    J -->|Yes| K["Label: Scam"]
    J -->|No| L["Label: Legitimate"]
    K --> M["Assign Risk Level"]
    L --> M
    M --> N["Return JSON Response"]
    N --> O["Frontend displays result with animated probability bar"]
```

### 5.4 API Request Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Browser (Frontend)
    participant CORS as CORS Middleware
    participant API as FastAPI App
    participant TF as TF-IDF + XGBoost
    participant FB as FinBERT + LR
    
    Client->>CORS: POST /predict {"text": "..."}
    CORS->>API: Pass request (all origins allowed)
    API->>API: Validate via Pydantic schema
    API->>API: clean_text(input)
    
    par Dual Engine
        API->>TF: vectorizer.transform → xgb.predict_proba
        TF-->>API: prob_scam_tfidf
        API->>FB: tokenizer → model → CLS → lr.predict_proba
        FB-->>API: prob_scam_finbert
    end
    
    API->>API: ensemble = 0.5*tfidf + 0.5*finbert
    API->>API: risk = High/Medium/Low
    API-->>Client: {"prediction", "probability", "risk_level"}
```

